<TEXT>
an itinerant painter sought for questioning in the 
killing of a kansas woman and the disappearances of three other 
women has decided to fight extradition authorities said saturday 
richard grissom jr 28 was captured friday by police and fbi 
agents at dallasfort worth international airport after an 
anonymous tipster told authorities grissom would be meeting an 
arriving passenger 
police in the kansas city suburb of overland park said jewelry 
and other belongings of at least one of the missing women were 
recovered at the airport from a car stolen in missouri that grissom 
allegedly drove to texas 
overland park police began seeking grissom an avid bodybuilder 
on june 27 in connection with the disappearance of 24yearold joan 
butler who was reported missing june 16 
kansas investigators also said grissom planned a date with terri 
maness 25 of wichita on june 7 the night she was strangled and 
stabbed repeatedly in her home 
police also want to question him about the disappearances of 
roommates theresa j brown and christine a rusch both 22 of 
lenexa kan keller said he was seen june 24 at a party given by 
the women who were reported missing june 26 
we found items linking the two women to him keller said 
credit cards and jewelry identified as belonging to one of the 
lenexa women were found in his car 
but authorities said grissom wasnt providing additional 
information about the three missing women 
he talks a lot and has admitted knowing the women but 
hes just not giving you anything you can make a case on said 
wichita police chief rick stone who was in dallas on personal 
business at the time of grissoms arrest 
keller said ms rusch was last seen using a bank card machine 
near grandview mo we have photos of her from the card machine 
and she appeared injured said keller she also made withdrawals 
totaling 2900 to 3200 he said 
so far keller said the three suburban kansas city women have 
not been found and only the body of the wichita kan woman has 
been recovered grissom has not been charged in the slaying or 
disappearances 
grissom is being held on kansas warrants for parole violation and 
felony theft he initially agreed to return to kansas to face the 
charges but decided saturday to fight extradition which can take 
60 to 90 days keller said 
grissom was convicted at age 16 of fatally bludgeoning a 
72yearold lansing kan woman with a railroad spike 
keller said grissom spoke with investigators friday about 
unsolved murder cases in missouri kansas and texas but he had not 
admitted being involved in any crimes 
