pti quoted leh police chief gj pandit as saying leh a city of 
100000 people is about 450 miles north of new delhi 
authorities on friday imposed an indefinite curfew on the city 
after clashes between buddhists and moslems authorities said the 
brawls were sparked by an argument between two youths 
several shops were set on fire and taxi drivers were dragged from 
