<TEXT>
the president on sunday gave foreign minister giulio 
andreotti a mandate to create the nations 49th postwar government 
and it appeared the fivetime premier would easily form a coalition 
italy has been without a government since may 19 when premier 
ciriaco de mita resigned following criticism of his leadership by 
the no 2 party in the governing coalition the socialists 
after president francesco cossiga summoned him sunday morning to 
receive the mandate andreotti said he would begin trying to form a 
government however he said his task might be delayed by 
preparations for this weeks meeting of the seven major 
industrialized nations in paris 
andreotti like de mita belongs to the christian democrats who 
have dominated italian politics since world war ii the de mita 
coalition apparently fell because of jockeying by the socialists 
led by popular former premier bettino craxi 
craxi said he would not oppose andreotti newspapers reported 
craxi and andreotti have worked closely in several governments 
de mitas policies would likely continue in an andreotti 
government the editor of the rome daily la repubblica eugenio 
scalfari noted in a frontpage editorial that andreotti and the 
leader of the christian democrats arnaldo forlani now hold the 
same positions as they did 17 years ago 
we are therefore about to turn back the clock of politics he 
said 
andreotti said he would work to revive the coalition of christian 
democrats socialists republicans liberals and social democrats 
that has governed in recent years 
he said he was particularly concerned that italy be ready for 
1992 when european community members are to eliminate all trade 
barriers among themselves 
andreotti is considered to come from the conservative wing of 
the christian democrats while de mita is a liberal however 
the labels can be misleading 
for example while andreotti is considered close to the roman 
catholic church the premierdesignate also has very good relations 
with the communists italys secondlargest party which has been in 
the opposition for more than 40 years 
andreotti 70 has been prominent in italian government since 
world war ii serving as premier twice in 197273 and three times 
successively in 197679 
