dozens were injured in a collision of fans on a ramp a soviet 
newspaper reported casualties at the time but did not specify 
whether people were killed or injured and did not give a number 
sovietsky sport reported on april 18 three days after 95 soccer 
fans were killed in a crush at hillsborough stadium in sheffield 
england that dozens of people were trampled to death in the 1982 
moscow incident 
the biggest loss of life previously reported at a soccer match 
was on may 24 1964 when rioting left nearly 300 dead in lima 
peru in a game between argentina and peru 
the worst singleincident sports disaster in modern history 
occurred when an estimated 604 people were killed after stands at 
the hong kong jockey club racecourse collapsed and caught fire in 
february 1918 
sovietsky sports said a minor stadium official was blamed for the 
1982 tragedy and sentenced to 18 months of corrective work but 
mostly the victims were blamed for alleged unruly behavior 
ever since the disaster no soccer matches have been held in 
lenin stadium at the end of october because authorities are afraid 
survivors will place flowers on the field as a sign of protest 
readers suggested a committee be set up to investigate the 
tragedy and that a meeting be held at the site oct 20 to 
commemorate the tragedy the newspaper said sunday 
the account was the latest disclosure by a soviet media that has 
seized upon president mikhail s gorbachevs policy of glasnost or 
openness to report long hushedup soviet disasters 
