gasoline prices continued an uncharacteristic 
summer decline caused by increased oil and gasoline supplies an 
analyst said sunday 
the nations average retail price for a gallon of gasoline was 
11676 on july 7 a decrease of 167 cents since early june said 
trilby lundberg publisher of the biweekly lundberg survey of 12000 
gas stations 
the price has dropped because refiners terminal operators and 
importers had increased supplies to meet new federal cleanair 
regulations lundberg said 
the drop reflects efforts on the part of the oil industry to 
step up their gasoline production and imports of gasoline during may 
and june in order to avoid any supply tightness or shortage 
lundberg said 
lundberg said that higher demand by summer drivers and policy 
changes in other oil producing nations could still push prices 
higher later this year 
